    "summary": "A flash fire occurred when an operator was draining vessels during maintenance preparation activities. Hydrocarbons backflowed from a depropanizer column through a leaking isolation valve into vessels being drained to the oil water sewer system. The hydrocarbons ignited at a nearby furnace, causing a flash fire that injured the operator.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Ensure procedures include steps for preparing all process equipment for maintenance",
      "Develop a process that requires pre-planning and hazard identification prior to initiating work",
      "Avoid relying on single block valves to control release of hazardous energy",
      "Initiate a process to evaluate hazards when isolation plans need modification",
      "Avoid draining materials containing hydrocarbons into sewer systems not designed for such services"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "flash fire",
      "maintenance preparation",
      "leaking valve",
      "backflow",
      "single block valve",
      "non-routine operations"
    ]
